designing in a way instead of

00:32:46.320 --> 00:32:47.810
pair programming.

00:32:47.810 --> 00:32:51.870
Or if you do print your work
out, set it flat on the table.

00:32:51.870 --> 00:32:54.530
Have both people sitting there
with the pens marking it up so

00:32:54.530 --> 00:32:58.210
it feels like it's very
collaborative.

00:32:58.210 --> 00:33:01.390
As you're defending reasons
that you did something, or

00:33:01.390 --> 00:33:03.420
you're trying not to have the
design be changed in a

00:33:03.420 --> 00:33:05.410
particular way.

00:33:05.410 --> 00:33:08.500
Don't say oh well,
I'm the designer,

00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:11.000
or that's my opinion.

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:13.650
Back it up with specific design
principles with actual

00:33:13.650 --> 00:33:15.540
reasons that are irrefutable
on why it

00:33:15.540 --> 00:33:16.350
needs to be that way.

00:33:16.350 --> 00:33:18.270
ROMAN NURIK: It's tough because
some things are so

00:33:18.270 --> 00:33:19.670
very subjective.

00:33:19.670 --> 00:33:22.180
Some things are just like, I
have this intuition, I can't

00:33:22.180 --> 00:33:22.590
explain it.

00:33:22.590 --> 00:33:25.780
But definitely, a big part of
the communication process is

00:33:25.780 --> 00:33:28.900
articulating what
you're thinking.

00:33:28.900 --> 00:33:30.610
ALEX FAABORG: Often it's
not subjective.

00:33:30.610 --> 00:33:33.490
There are actual reasons
why something should

00:33:33.490 --> 00:33:34.810
be a certain way--

00:33:34.810 --> 00:33:39.460
underlying cognitive science
and design principles.

00:33:39.460 --> 00:33:41.640
Or even just existing
user studies.

00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:43.960
If you have done a user study
yourself, there are previous

00:33:43.960 --> 00:33:45.860
user studies that point to the
same results that you can

00:33:45.860 --> 00:33:47.900
anticipate.

00:33:47.900 --> 00:33:58.260
So it's very important to make
sure that your take on the

00:33:58.260 --> 00:34:00.210
design is dripping in science.

00:34:00.210 --> 00:34:03.120
Because if it's just my opinion
versus your opinion,

00:34:03.120 --> 00:34:06.630
then you could just continue
debating forever.

00:34:06.630 --> 00:34:09.514
Engineers don't debate
oh, well, I think it

00:34:09.514 --> 00:34:10.630
